Bootstrap Grid. 

Uses Containers, Rows, and Columns to create a Layout. 

Containers. 
Containers provide a means to center and horizontally pad your siteâ€™s contents. 
Use .container for a responsive pixel width 
or .container-fluid for width: 100% across all viewport and device sizes.

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm">
      One of three columns
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm">
      One of three columns
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm">
      One of three columns
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```
